===Etymology===
From {{Sp.}} [[cinco]] "five" + [[de#Spanish|de]] "of" [[Mayo]] "May"
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[cinco|Cinco]] [[de]] [[Mayo]]'''

#A [[national]] celebration in [[Mexico]]. It commemorates the victory of Mexican forces led by General Ignacio Zaragoza over the [[French]] [[expeditionary]] forces in the Battle of Puebla on May 5, 1862. The date is also celebrated widely by [[immigrants]] living in the [[United States]].

